  <properties>
    <title>Goto a folder</title>
  </properties>

  <body>
    <section name="Goto a Folder">
      <span class="shortdesc">How to get to a folder, to add or change content in it.</span>

   <script type="text/javascript">
    leftpx=0;
    bottompx=600;
   </script>
   <div class='group'> 
    <div id='screenshot'><div>
     <img src="../../../../images/screenshots/cms_M9/contribs/goto_folder.png" alt='Goto folder screenshot'/>
    </div></div> 
     <p>
        Marc clicks on the foldername 'newspaper', to go to that folder, i.e. make it the 
        <a href='../concepts/current_folder.html'>current folder</a>.
        He will see the ontent of the newspaper folder
        tabulated in the <a href='../concepts/content_tabulation_panel.html'>
        content tabulation panel</a> and he         
        will be allowed to create a new document in that folder.
    </p>
   </div>

   <p>
      In the <a href='../concepts/content_navigation_panel.html'>content navigation panel</a>,
      within the documents <a href='../concepts/slider.html'>slider</a>, the names of all folders
      for <a href='../concepts/document.html'>documents</a> are shown.
      <span class='add'>Document about navigation in folder tree and reference from here.</span>
   </p>
   <p>
      Clicking on a foldername will bring you to the folder, i.e. make it the 
      <a href='../concepts/current_folder.html'>current folder</a>.
      The contents of the current folder will appear in 
      the <a href='../concepts/content_tabulation_panel.html'>
      content tabulation panel.</a>
      It is also possible to do 
      <a href='../concepts/folder_action.html'>folder actions</a> on it, like
      adding a new document.
   </p>

